timing_report...aths_per_group(25.10)    timing_report...aths_per_group(25.10)

Name
       timing_report_disable_max_paths_per_group

Syntax
       timing_report_disable_max_paths_per_group {true | false}

       Default: false

       Controls  the  interpretation of the report_timing -max_paths parameter
       when you request reporting across a set  of  path  groups.  By  default
       (false  setting),  the  specified  -max_paths will be reported per path
       group. With the true setting, a total of the specified -max_paths  will
       be reported across all of the specified path groups.

       For Stylus flow cross-tool compatibility - you should specify a setting
       of  true.  For  backward  compatibility  with  the legacy UI flow - you
       should use a value of false.

       For example,

       When set to false:

       Legacy UI:  report_timing -path_group {reg2reg in2reg} -nworst 2 ...

       Stylus UI:  report_timing -group {reg2reg in2reg} -nworst 2 ...

       The report_timing command will return up to 2  paths  for  the  reg2reg
       group and also up to 2 paths for the in2reg group.

       When set to true:

       Legacy UI: set timing_report_disable_max_paths_per_group true

       Stylus UI: set_db timing_report_disable_max_paths_per_group true

       A  total of 2 paths will be reported across both path groups. The paths
       may come entirely from one or the other group - or both, based  on  the
       slack value.

       To set this global variable, use the set command.

